542
00:28:46.127 --> 00:28:48.713
Not on the car I drive my kids
to school in everyday.

543
00:28:50.409 --> 00:28:52.811
Do you mind?!

544
00:28:52.912 --> 00:28:55.480
Had to have been that woman who
was staring at me the other night.

545
00:28:55.581 --> 00:28:57.143
Was she driving
a silver Mercedes?

546
00:28:57.168 --> 00:28:58.368
Yeah. It was parked
right over there.

547
00:28:59.118 --> 00:29:01.820
Must have been Valerie Dawson.
Jared's wife.

548
00:29:01.921 --> 00:29:03.955
Wait. She knows
that I give Jared massages?

549
00:29:04.056 --> 00:29:05.390
Oh. honey.
she's all bark.

550
00:29:05.491 --> 00:29:07.659
You know. she's made
some crazy threats before.

551
00:29:07.760 --> 00:29:09.461
Wait a minute.
It's happened before?

552
00:29:09.562 --> 00:29:12.297
And you didn't do anything about
it? Why didn't you tell me?

553
00:29:12.398 --> 00:29:15.367
Well. I don't like to upset my girls.
So you just ignore it?

554
00:29:15.468 --> 00:29:17.169
Look. I can't come out
to my car like this.

555
00:29:17.270 --> 00:29:19.037
Unlike you. I've got a family
to worry about.

556
00:29:19.138 --> 00:29:20.906
Well.
my girls are my family.

557
00:29:21.007 --> 00:29:24.009
and I have been running
a nice. successful business here

558
00:29:24.110 --> 00:29:26.278
for the last three years
all by myself.

559
00:29:26.379 --> 00:29:29.748
ever since my husband left me
with one of my girls!

560
00:29:30.750 --> 00:29:34.286
Clean your own damn car!

561
00:29:35.354 --> 00:29:37.022
Georgia!

562
00:29:46.299 --> 00:29:49.167
What the hell are you doing?
Mowing your yard.

563
00:29:49.268 --> 00:29:50.569
Well.
no one asked you to.

564
00:29:50.670 --> 00:29:52.938
Put your shirt back on.
The neighbors are staring.

565
00:29:53.039 --> 00:29:55.440
Just wanted to help.
Riley.

566
00:29:55.541 --> 00:29:56.908
I know you've been busy
with your new job.

567
00:29:57.009 --> 00:29:59.010
Well.
that's Kyle's job. so...

568
00:29:59.111 --> 00:30:00.912
But he's not
here anymore.

569
00:30:06.118 --> 00:30:09.120
I'll see you later.

570
00:30:25.872 --> 00:30:27.272
Hey. sweetheart.

571
00:30:27.373 --> 00:30:30.642
Can we talk
for a minute?

572
00:30:30.743 --> 00:30:34.012
So. I just got off the phone
with Mr. Marshall.

573
00:30:34.113 --> 00:30:37.082
and he said that
you are not participating

574
00:30:37.183 --> 00:30:39.484
in the rehearsals
for Spring Sing.

575
00:30:39.585 --> 00:30:41.152
You know the dance now.
You love to sing.

576
00:30:41.254 --> 00:30:43.922
What does it matter
if daddy won't be there?

577
00:30:44.023 --> 00:30:45.824
He won't be back.
will he?

578
00:30:47.760 --> 00:30:51.162
Baby. right now I'm not sure
when he's gonna be back.

579
00:30:51.264 --> 00:30:53.899
But. hey.
I do know this.

580
00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.968
He loves you so much.

581
00:30:57.069 --> 00:31:01.573
More than anything.
just like I do.

582
00:31:01.674 --> 00:31:03.575
You know what?

583
00:31:03.676 --> 00:31:06.945
You do not have to
be in the Spring Sing.

584
00:31:07.046 --> 00:31:09.814
I will call Mr. Marshall
tomorrow morning.

585
00:31:09.916 --> 00:31:11.283
Let me sleep with it.

586
00:31:11.384 --> 00:31:13.919
Or sleep on it?

587
00:31:14.020 --> 00:31:15.654
Okay.

588
00:31:15.755 --> 00:31:16.988
Eskimo kiss.

589
00:31:34.040 --> 00:31:37.175
Hey. You okay?
It's late.

590
00:31:37.276 --> 00:31:39.110
We need to talk.

591
00:31:43.149 --> 00:31:46.184
I know how you've been making all
that money at that new job of yours.

592
00:31:49.622 --> 00:31:51.022
What the hell
are you talking about?

593
00:31:51.123 --> 00:31:53.024
Well. I was out.
having a few beers.

594
00:31:53.125 --> 00:31:56.661
and it was so obvious once
I started thinking about it.

595
00:31:56.762 --> 00:31:59.331
so why don't you just come out
and admit it. Riley?

596
00:31:59.432 --> 00:32:02.167
I mean. Kyle's hardly gone.
and you stoop to this.

597
00:32:02.268 --> 00:32:03.568
What's his name?

598
00:32:03.669 --> 00:32:05.403
Whose name?

599
00:32:05.504 --> 00:32:06.838
Your sugar daddy.

600
00:32:08.507 --> 00:32:10.408
You think I have
a sugar daddy?

601
00:32:10.509 --> 00:32:12.477
Yeah.
From work. right?

602
00:32:12.578 --> 00:32:14.646
I mean. a friend of mine
at the bank said you came in

603
00:32:14.747 --> 00:32:16.915
and you paid your mortgage
in cash.

604
00:32:17.016 --> 00:32:19.417
How else could you be bringing
home that kind of money?

605
00:32:19.518 --> 00:32:20.919
Wow.

606
00:32:21.020 --> 00:32:25.523
Wow. That is so...
that's so insulting.

607
00:32:25.624 --> 00:32:27.359
I mean. I happen to be
very good at my job.

608
00:32:27.460 --> 00:32:29.694
Why is that so hard
for everybody to understand?!

609
00:32:29.795 --> 00:32:31.496
'Cause it doesn't add up.
That's why!

610
00:32:31.597 --> 00:32:33.898
I'll tell you
what adds up!

611
00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:35.567
I am fighting tooth and nail
to provide for my family

612
00:32:35.668 --> 00:32:37.836
after the most traumatic event
in my life.

613
00:32:37.937 --> 00:32:39.170
Your brother...
Settle down.

614
00:32:39.271 --> 00:32:41.006
...walking out on me.
and the last thing I need

615
00:32:41.107 --> 00:32:42.832
is you coming over here
after a few drinks...

616
00:32:42.857 --> 00:32:43.942
Look. I just --
I just was --

617
00:32:43.943 --> 00:32:45.910
...making wild accusations! No! What?!
I just was --

618
00:32:46.012 --> 00:32:47.812
I just was -- what?! I was
just confused! That's what!

619
00:32:47.913 --> 00:32:49.547
God.
How drunk are you?

620
00:32:51.250 --> 00:32:52.817
Riley. look. You --

621
00:32:52.918 --> 00:32:55.186
No. Now. you have said enough.
You go home.

622
00:32:55.287 --> 00:32:57.522
And why don't you keep your
crazy judgments about my life

623
00:32:57.623 --> 00:32:59.391
to yourself from now on.

624
00:32:59.492 --> 00:33:02.594
You got that?
Now. get on out of here.

625
00:33:20.646 --> 00:33:23.548
Hell. you'd think we'd be busier
with the rodeo in town.

626
00:33:23.649 --> 00:33:25.884
The gay rodeo. Jolene.
Didn't you read the signs?

627
00:33:25.985 --> 00:33:27.452
The gay rodeo?
You kidding me?

628
00:33:27.553 --> 00:33:29.888
Count me in.
Sounds frisky.

629
00:33:29.989 --> 00:33:31.322
Is nothing sacred?

630
00:33:33.959 --> 00:33:36.094
At least somebody's
busy today.

631
00:33:36.195 --> 00:33:37.862
I heard about your special
therapy sessions with Jared Dawson.

632
00:33:37.963 --> 00:33:41.433
He's been singing your praises
to anyone who'll listen.

633
00:33:41.534 --> 00:33:43.535
You do know clients
don't come in here to talk.

634
00:33:43.636 --> 00:33:45.770
Well.
I was just trying to help.

635
00:33:45.871 --> 00:33:47.338
Not so smart long-term.

636
00:33:47.440 --> 00:33:50.108
Sending the clients
back to their wives.

637
00:33:50.209 --> 00:33:51.910
I think he just wanted to
be listened to.

638
00:33:52.011 --> 00:33:53.211
Like we all do.

639
00:33:53.312 --> 00:33:55.213
Sorry. honey. but you
don't get to make decisions

640
00:33:55.314 --> 00:33:56.781
that affect all of us.

641
00:33:56.882 --> 00:33:58.416
Maybe you just
feel guilty.

642
00:33:58.517 --> 00:34:00.151
They don't have
what you have --

643
00:34:00.252 --> 00:34:02.587
