to come home to every night.

644
00:34:04.423 --> 00:34:07.659
Um. not so perfect.

645
00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:09.294
Kyle left me
right after I started here.

646
00:34:09.395 --> 00:34:12.030
and I have no idea
if he's ever coming back.

647
00:34:19.839 --> 00:34:23.108
What did you do?
I didn't know.

648
00:34:23.209 --> 00:34:25.777
Hey.
I was looking for you.

649
00:34:25.878 --> 00:34:28.113
Why? So you can
get all upset again?

650
00:34:28.214 --> 00:34:29.447
I'm sorry about that.

651
00:34:29.548 --> 00:34:31.282
I didn't know
that your husband had left you.

652
00:34:31.383 --> 00:34:33.785
His loss.
I'm doing just fine on my own.

653
00:34:33.886 --> 00:34:35.353
You know. the thing is

654
00:34:35.454 --> 00:34:37.422
I just can't have people
writing on my car like that.

655
00:34:37.523 --> 00:34:39.924
I get it.
No job is perfect.

656
00:34:40.025 --> 00:34:42.794
I wish I could control the
entire universe. but I can't.

657
00:34:42.895 --> 00:34:44.295
It's more than that.

658
00:34:44.396 --> 00:34:47.432
I just want a job
that I can feel proud of.

659
00:34:47.533 --> 00:34:49.434
Trust me. honey.
We all do.

660
00:34:49.535 --> 00:34:52.203
I'm just not sure that this
is the right thing for me.

661
00:34:52.304 --> 00:34:55.540
Well. that's something
you're gonna have to figure out

662
00:34:55.641 --> 00:34:57.709
on your own.

663
00:35:15.834 --> 00:35:20.071
Oh. you have goto be
kidding me.

664
00:35:20.172 --> 00:35:23.408
You're Valerie Dawson. right?
You wrote all over my car.

665
00:35:23.509 --> 00:35:24.909
Are you out of
your freaking mind?

666
00:35:25.010 --> 00:35:26.978
I don't know
what you're talking about.

667
00:35:27.079 --> 00:35:29.280
But I want you
to stay away from my husband.

668
00:35:29.381 --> 00:35:31.182
Nothing is going on
with me and Jared.

669
00:35:31.283 --> 00:35:32.917
I'm just listening to him.

670
00:35:33.018 --> 00:35:34.529
Oh. and I suppose he hasn't
done anything with any of

671
00:35:34.554 --> 00:35:36.064
those other girls. either.

672
00:35:36.255 --> 00:35:37.622
I honestly don't know.

673
00:35:37.723 --> 00:35:39.357
But when he's with me.
on my table.

674
00:35:39.458 --> 00:35:42.427
he is telling me
how much he loves you.

675
00:35:42.528 --> 00:35:45.363
I find that
very hard to believe.

676
00:35:45.464 --> 00:35:46.764
Do you know

677
00:35:46.865 --> 00:35:49.534
that he doesn't think you give
a crap about him anymore?

678
00:35:49.635 --> 00:35:51.669
He thinks you just care more
about your friends

679
00:35:51.770 --> 00:35:53.371
and your charities
than you do him.

680
00:35:53.472 --> 00:35:54.872
That's ridiculous.

681
00:35:54.973 --> 00:35:56.441
Then why does he feel
so lonely?

682
00:35:56.542 --> 00:36:00.778
Look. I know that there are
two sides to this. but trust me.

683
00:36:00.879 --> 00:36:03.281
A man does not
go looking elsewhere

684
00:36:03.382 --> 00:36:05.316
if he's getting what he needs
at home.

685
00:36:09.088 --> 00:36:13.324
Oh. hell.

686
00:36:13.425 --> 00:36:16.160
You're not getting
what you need. either. are you?

687
00:36:17.796 --> 00:36:21.065
But there was a time
you were.

688
00:36:21.166 --> 00:36:22.567
He told me.

689
00:36:24.169 --> 00:36:26.938
If you love him.
you still have a chance.

690
00:36:32.077 --> 00:36:34.312
What should I do?

691
00:36:34.413 --> 00:36:36.080
Tell him
you want him back.

692
00:36:36.181 --> 00:36:38.149
And that whatever he's done.

693
00:36:38.250 --> 00:36:40.084
it's in the past.
it's over.

694
00:36:40.185 --> 00:36:43.388
You love him.
and you want to move on.

695
00:36:43.489 --> 00:36:47.024
Why are you crying?

696
00:36:47.126 --> 00:36:48.559
Because that's something

697
00:36:48.660 --> 00:36:51.162
I'll probably never
get the chance to do.

698
00:36:51.263 --> 00:36:54.432
But you can do it right now.
You can go home.

699
00:36:55.801 --> 00:36:58.169
And then screw the living
daylights out of him.

700
00:37:04.176 --> 00:37:05.743
Good luck.

701
00:37:05.844 --> 00:37:07.612
Same to you.

702
00:37:17.689 --> 00:37:20.258
Mommy.
I used too much hair gel.

703
00:37:20.359 --> 00:37:21.993
It's gonna ruin the show!

704
00:37:22.094 --> 00:37:24.729
Good lord.
You look like a wet possum.

705
00:37:24.830 --> 00:37:26.531
Mama.
that's really not helping.

706
00:37:26.632 --> 00:37:28.566
Now. Travis.
I said just to use a dab.

707
00:37:28.667 --> 00:37:31.102
Well. daddy always
helps me do it.

708
00:37:31.203 --> 00:37:33.805
It's okay.
I can fix this.

709
00:37:33.906 --> 00:37:36.474
It's nothing compared to
the disasters down at the salon.

710
00:37:36.575 --> 00:37:37.608
Come on. possum.

711
00:37:37.709 --> 00:37:40.344
Oh. no.

712
00:37:42.047 --> 00:37:45.450
Katie.
you look so cute.

713
00:37:45.551 --> 00:37:47.051
Hey. I thought you weren't
gonna be in the show.

714
00:37:47.152 --> 00:37:48.152
What made you
change your mind?

715
00:37:48.253 --> 00:37:50.288
I want you to be proud
of me.

716
00:37:50.389 --> 00:37:52.790
Oh. baby. I always am.

717
00:37:54.259 --> 00:37:56.828
Now got get your brother
'cause he's running late.

718
00:37:59.665 --> 00:38:01.766
Oh!

719
00:38:03.836 --> 00:38:07.305
Um. I-I just wanted to say
something real quick.

720
00:38:07.406 --> 00:38:09.807
Yeah. Okay.
Come on in.

721
00:38:12.010 --> 00:38:15.112
Look. I -- I'm real sorry
about that sugar-daddy comment

722
00:38:15.214 --> 00:38:16.614
the other night.

723
00:38:16.715 --> 00:38:17.949
I-it was totally
out of line.

724
00:38:18.050 --> 00:38:20.151
It upset you.
I-I was real drunk.

725
00:38:20.252 --> 00:38:21.752
You weren't that drunk.
Evan.

726
00:38:21.854 --> 00:38:23.788
You gonna make this
even harder than it is?

727
00:38:23.889 --> 00:38:25.923
Besides. the backyard
still needs to be mowed.

728
00:38:26.024 --> 00:38:28.092
Let me -- let me
at least do that.

729
00:38:28.193 --> 00:38:30.495
Promise to keep my shirt on
this time.

730
00:38:32.998 --> 00:38:34.332
Fine.

731
00:38:34.433 --> 00:38:36.000
And I can go
to the kids' show. right?

732
00:38:36.101 --> 00:38:37.535
Yes. of course you can.

733
00:38:37.636 --> 00:38:39.415
Okay.
Want me to shut this?

734
00:38:39.440 --> 00:38:40.640
Please.

735
00:38:40.806 --> 00:38:41.973
It's a good look for you.
by the way.

736
00:38:42.074 --> 00:38:45.209
Go.

737
00:38:53.218 --> 00:38:54.852
For the first time
in 30 years.

738
00:38:54.953 --> 00:38:56.954
I think Riley
might just take my advice.

739
00:38:57.055 --> 00:38:58.456
Tell my boss he does --

740
00:38:58.557 --> 00:39:00.391
mama.
We're here to watch the show.

741
00:39:00.492 --> 00:39:01.959
Riley!

742
00:39:02.060 --> 00:39:03.227
Riley!

743
00:39:06.899 --> 00:39:07.999
I'll be right back.

744
00:39:08.100 --> 00:39:11.569
Hey. Hey.

745
00:39:11.670 --> 00:39:13.804
I can't believe
you're here.

746
00:39:13.906 --> 00:39:15.640
I just happened
to be in the neighborhood.

747
00:39:15.741 --> 00:39:18.175
Come on.

748
00:39:19.645 --> 00:39:21.612
This is the last place
I expected to see you.

749
00:39:21.713 --> 00:39:23.881
I'm pretty determined
when I have something to say.

750
00:39:23.982 --> 00:39:26.384
Okay.
I'm listening.

751
00:39:26.485 --> 00:39:27.785
You were right.

752
00:39:27.886 --> 00:39:29.587
It's important
to feel safe.

753
00:39:29.688 --> 00:39:32.089
so I had cameras installed
outside the spa.

754
00:39:32.190 --> 00:39:33.624
Cost me
an arm and a leg.

755
00:39:33.725 --> 00:39:36.027
I'm sure the girls
will really appreciate it.

756
00:39:36.128 --> 00:39:37.728
Does that include you?

757
00:39:37.829 --> 00:39:39.830
I'm still
wrestling with it.

758
00:39:39.932 --> 00:39:44.001
Maybe it would help if you knew
Jared swung by this morning.

759
00:39:44.102 --> 00:39:46.671
Said he's taking his wife
to Hawaii for a week.

760
00:39:46.772 --> 00:39:47.705
Oh. that's great.

761
00:39:47.806 --> 00:39:49.206
Yes. it is.

762
00:39:49.308 --> 00:39:50.474
In all these years.

763
00:39:50.576 --> 00:39:53.678
I've never known one of my girls
to save a marriage.

764
00:39:53.779 --> 00:39:56.881
You have a funny effect
on people. don't you?

765
00:39:56.982 --> 00:39:59.617
Yeah. they either love me
or haul ass.

766
00:39:59.718 --> 00:40:03.621
Well. I love you. honey.
and no matter what you decide.

767
00:40:03.722 --> 00:40:08.559
I hope we remain friends
because  I'd miss you.

768
00:40:08.660 --> 00:40:12.063
No one's ever
chased me down before.

769
00:40:12.164 --> 00:40:14.098
Feels good.

770
00:40:14.199 --> 00:40:16.100
Well. anybody that would
put you in their rearview mirror

771
00:40:16.201 --> 00:40:17.668
is a fool.

772
00:40:19.237 --> 00:40:20.471
You know what. Georgia?

773
00:40:20.572 --> 00:40:22.807
I may not have been
able to save my marriage.

774
00:40:22.908 --> 00:40:25.376
but I'm gonna save
my family.

775
00:40:25.477 --> 00:40:28.279
I'm glad to hear it.

776
00:40:28.380 --> 00:40:30.915
I'll see you tomorrow.

777
00:40:52.037 --> 00:40:55.006
I think we can
skip P.J.s tonight.

778
00:40:55.107 --> 00:40:57.508
They were awesome.

779
00:40:57.609 --> 00:41:00.177
Katie looked like she was having
such a great time.

780
00:41:00.278 --> 00:41:02.279
I'm so proud of them.

781
00:41:08.954 --> 00:41:11.022
You know.
I'm proud of you.

782
00:41:11.123 --> 00:41:12.857
What for?

783
00:41:12.958 --> 00:41:17.294
Somehow managing
to keep it all together.

784
00:41:17.396 --> 00:41:19.964
The kids. the house.

785
00:41:20.065 --> 00:41:21.298
It's a lot.

786
00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:23.401
Well.
I had a little help.

787
00:41:23.502 --> 00:41:26.270
You know. I think you're a lot
stronger than anyone ever knew.

788
00:41:28.640 --> 00:41:29.573
Thank you.

789
00:41:29.675 --> 00:41:32.343
And if you
ever need anything...

790
00:41:32.444 --> 00:41:33.978
I know.

791
00:41:41.586 --> 00:41:44.255
Oh. my God.

792
00:41:44.322 --> 00:41:47.491
It's Kyle.

793
00:41:51.276 --> 00:41:53.210
Hello?

794
00:41:53.235 --> 00:41:57.235
